<subSubSection id="C315BF87FFFEFFF40DF652CF2196FD07" box="[151,909,725,747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB0EC0CFFFEFFF40DF652CF2196FD07" blockId="5.[151,909,725,747]" box="[151,909,725,747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The 
<typeStatus id="54B452AEFFFEFFF40DA552CC22EBFD07" box="[196,240,726,747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species for this subgenus is 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F978FFFFEFFF40F7152CF2192FD07" authority="Kotthaus, 1969" authorityName="Kotthaus" authorityYear="1969" box="[528,905,725,747]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40F7152CF20FDFD07" box="[528,742,725,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cypselurus formosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E91FDFFFEFFF40F8A52CF2192FD07" author="Kotthaus, A." box="[747,905,725,747]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref51616" refString="Kotthaus, A. (1969) Fische des Indischen Ozeans. A. Systematischer Teil IV: Synentognathi. Meteor Forschungsergebnisse, Reihe D, Biologie, H. 4, 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1969">Kotthaus, 1969</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C315BF87FFFEFFF40DF6530D2689FC71" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB0EC0CFFFEFFF40DF6530D2689FC71" blockId="5.[151,1436,791,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40DF6530D23B8FCDC" bold="true" box="[151,419,791,816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
This subgenus differs from all other subgenera of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F978FFFFEFFF409EB53022700FCDC" authorityName="Lowe" authorityYear="1840" box="[1162,1307,792,816]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF409EB53022700FCDC" box="[1162,1307,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cheilopogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in smaller number of vertebrae and in the absence of chin barbels and enlarged dorsal fin (&quot;Parexocoetus&quot; stage) in juveniles (this stage is also absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F978FFFFEFFF40CAD537A2055FC94" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1843" box="[460,590,864,888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="68" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ptenichthys">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40CAD537A2055FC94" box="[460,590,864,888]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ptenichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). From the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F978FFFFEFFF40E7C537A2180FC94" baseAuthorityName="sensu Parin" baseAuthorityYear="1961" box="[797,923,864,888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40E7C537A2180FC94" box="[797,923,864,888]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs in an elongate lower jaw protruding in front of the upper jaw, and in the presence of sharp (often recurved) unicuspid jaw teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C315BF87FFFEFFF40DA653BD21D7FBBC" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB0EC0CFFFEFFF40DA653BD212BFBEB" blockId="5.[151,1436,791,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40DA653BD2355FC2C" bold="true" box="[199,334,935,960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the subgenus reflects the characteristics of the 
<typeStatus id="54B452AEFFFEFFF40E9D53B22637FC2C" box="[1020,1068,936,960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
species—the absence of barbels in juveniles and the presence of strong teeth on the jaws (from the Greek words Aµoυστάκoς (amustacas)—having no barbels and Περιτρώγoν (peritrógon)—toothed creature.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0EC0CFFFEFFF40DA6540E21D7FBBC" blockId="5.[151,1436,791,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40DA6540E2025FBC1" bold="true" box="[199,574,1044,1069]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Composition of the subgenus.</emphasis>
We include two species in the subgenus: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F978FFFFEFFF4092D540E2366FBBC" authority="(Kotthaus)" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Kotthaus" baseAuthorityYear="1969" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus" subGenus="Amustotrogon">
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF4092D540E26C6FBC0" box="[1100,1245,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Cheilopogon</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40994540E2788FBC7" box="[1269,1427,1044,1067]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Amustotrogon</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40DF6542222E5FBBC" box="[151,254,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">formosus</emphasis>
(Kotthaus)
</taxonomicName>
(with 3 subspecies) and 
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40FF3542220A8FBBC" box="[658,691,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ch</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F978FFFFEFFF40FA154222170FBBC" authority="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin, 2019" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2019" box="[704,875,1080,1104]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cheilopogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marisrubri" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Amustotrogon">
(
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40FAB542220C0FBA3" box="[714,731,1080,1103]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40F9354222170FBBC" box="[754,875,1080,1104]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">marisrubri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97B301EFFFEFFF40E12542D21D7FBBC" bold="true" box="[883,972,1079,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2488D65FFFEFFF40E12542D21D7FBBC" box="[883,972,1079,1104]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
